The following figure shows the panel „Customer Contracts“. This panel displays the existing customer contracts of a customer. The panel consists of several embedded panels, which are used to create new customer contracts or to gather informations about the existing contracts.

In case that at least one customer contract exists for the customer, the panel “Customer Contract” is displayed in red color to inform the user at a glance.


Panel Master Data – Customer Contracts - Contract
The panel „Master Data – Customer Contract“ contains eight further panels. The first panel „Contract“ shows the contract number, the start date of the contract and primary and secondary unit the contract is valid for. At the time of the contracts’ conclusion and at the end date of the contract the transmission of an automatic contract confirmation can be defined. The option of an additional contract information on every invoice can be checked here as well.

The user can select, whether the confirmation should be created using a batch process or directly. The latter function can be started with the button next to the checkbox. After creating a document directly the checkbox will be disabled to avoid the creation of the same document again during the batch process.


Figure 80: Complete View of the Contract Panel

Creation of a new Customer Contract
The basis for the evaluation and the settlement is a cutstomer contract. These contracts are frameworks with several common characteristics, options and properties. Some of the characteristics depend on the type of the customer contract.

Using the panel „Customer Contracts – Contract“ a new contract can be entered. The empty panel looks like described in the next figure and contains some default settings. The possible data entries are described in the following section:

· Contract Class: For which kind of orders the contract is valid?

· Advertisments;

· Supplements;

· Turnover;

· Contract Date, when the contract has been concluded;

· Primary Accounting Unit: Primary accounting unit of the contract, which is not necessarily identical with the unit of the achievement or the geometric size of an advertisement. The following  units are possible:

· for advertisement achievements:

· column millimeters;

· publication count;

· currency unit (turnover);

· for supplement achievements:

· supplement count;

· currency unit (turnover);

· Secondary Accounting Unit: Optionally a secondary accounting unit scale can be defined for a contract. This unit always is a advertisement count unit as an alternative for the unit column millimeters. If a secondary unit is defined for the customer contract, the system always evaluates the contract discount on basis of the unit more advantageous for the customer.

· Control of customer contract correspondence:

· start and end of the contract;

· current level of the contract on every customers’ invoice.


