This functionality is responsible for the creation an the shipment of invoices. Depending on the customers’ settings it is possible to create single and collect invoices in a weekly, decadely (ten days) and monthly frequency.

Moreover different options of bundling and separating invoices can be considered. For example it is possible to create a single invoice for a specific order, although the customer normally gets a monthly invoice. Credits can be separated from invoices, invoices may be separated by commercial objects, editions and contractors.

Invoice Structure
The setup of an invoice distinguishes between the invoice data (which are freezed in the database) the structure of these data and the corporate design of the printed documents. With the use of XSL stylesheets the design of the invoice document can be influenced on several levels (e.g. commercial object) and may lead to a completely different design of the invoices. Variable Data can be printed on the invoice on demand.

A print proof on the invoice can be achieved with different options (e.g. grayscale or color print, maximal size, minimal zoom factor, proof on the back side of the sheet or on separate sheet(s)). A form for bank transfers can be included.

For the creation of invoices four different hierarchical levels are used: invoice header, invoice position, invoice subposition and invoice subposition part. The meaning of the different levels are explained following. All levels finally are used to „freeze“ all needed data from different sources to be able to create the similar invoice at every time.

Even if there are no legal restrictions the current structure of the invoice data don’t allow the use of different VAT rate on one invoice (invoices with different VAT rates are actually separated).


Invoice Header
The invoice header is the first hierarchy level of an invoice and contains all global invoice data:

· Address of invoice recipient;
· Delivering company (e.g. German Post or UPS);
· Address of the customer (in case of an agency order;
· Invoice number;
· Invoice number range;
· Customer number;
· Invoice title (e.g. „Invoice“ or „Credit“)
· Bank Transfer Form;
· Payment hint (e.g. „Net Payment within 14 Days“);
· Tax-ID of invoice recipient;
· Tax-ID of contractor (company);
· Current Customer Contract Standings;
· Sconto Percentage Sconto for Bank Transfers;
· Sconto Amount for Bank Transfers;
· Gross Payment Amount;
· Net Payment Amount;
· VAT Percentage;
· VAT Amount.

Invoice Postion
The invoice position is the second hierarchy level of the invoice. It groups several ads to positions, which achievement type (e.g. ad or supplement), edition and edition part is identical. This level has been added to the three common levels to achive a higher flexibility for the invoice design. The invoice position contains the following data:

· Invoice Position Number
